# Contribution Guidelines

Thank you for considering contributing to HolidayHub! We welcome contributions from the community to enhance the project. Please follow these guidelines:

## Reporting Issues

If you encounter any issues or have suggestions, please open an [issue](../../issues). Provide detailed information, including steps to reproduce the problem.

## Making Contributions

1. Fork the repository.
2. Create a new branch for your feature or bug fix: `git checkout -b feature/your-feature` or `git checkout -b bugfix/your-bug-fix`.
3. Commit your changes: `git commit -m "Add your feature"`.
4. Push to the branch: `git push origin feature/your-feature`.
5. Open a Pull Request (PR) against the `main` branch.

## Code Style

Follow the existing code style and conventions. Make sure your code is readable and well-documented.

## Feature Requests

If you have ideas for new features, feel free to open an issue to discuss them.

## Contact

For questions or discussions, you can reach out through [LinkedIn](https://www.linkedin.com/in/sydur-rahman).

Thank you for contributing to HolidayHub!
